Molefi Ntseki, coach of South Africa reacts during the international friendly match between South Africa and Zambia at Royal Bafokeng Stadium, Rustenburg, on 11 October JOHANNESBURG - Molefi Ntseki has been fired as Bafana Bafana coach. Ntseki failed to qualify South Africa for the 2022 Afcon tournament in Cameroon. READ: Bafana Bafana lose in Sudan to miss out on Afcon Bafana lost 2-0 to Sudan in their last Afcon qualifier. Ntseki took over from Stuart Baxter in 2019.